		<span class="subhead">Benoit&nbsp;Bisson</span><br>
		<strong>Benoit Bisson enr.</strong><br>
		Journalist 
		<br>
		</td>
		
		<td width="20">&nbsp;</td>
		
		<td width="420" valign="top">		
		Benoit Bisson is an editor/journalist based in Montreal, Canada, who has been involved in covering technology for nearly 10 years, and has been working in journalism for over 25 years. He is currently working freelance for a number of Montreal-based magazines, writing product reviews and features. Previously, he was in charge of the Techno-Sciences section of the Canoe Web portal - a division of Quebecor Media - a French language information portal averaging 30 million impressions monthly. Prior to that, he was the editor-in-chief of Sympatico Magazine, a bi-monthly print magazine with a circulation of 250,000. The magazine provided insight to readers on consumer trends as well as product reviews and how-to articles about the Internet and the use of Internet and computer-related products. In the mid-90's, while working as editor of the Maclean Hunter trade publication "Quincaillerie Matériaux", he initiated the launch of an online version of the magazine, one of the first such publications in Canada.<br>
