		<img src="/shared_files/innovation_judges/2004/Judge139.jpg"><br>
		
		
		<span class="subhead">Peter&nbsp;Bressler</span><br>
		<strong>BresslerGroup Inc.</strong><br>
		Principal 
		<br>
		</td>
		
		<td width="20">&nbsp;</td>
		
		<td width="420" valign="top">		
		Peter is the leader of the product planning and development group at Bresslergroup.  The group is known for its successful user centered product design solutions in a wide range of markets including industrial, commercial, medical, electronics, and consumer products.  Peter is a hands-on project director who is involved in the design process on a daily basis.  His particular strengths include project management, user research, human factors application, manufacturing processes and innovative criteria conflict resolution.  He has authored or co-authored over 70 design and utility patents. Peter Has received over 50 national and international awards for product design, design engineering, packaging design and graphics.

Peter and Bresslergroup serve a broad range of national and international clients including; Becton Dickinson, Black and Decker, The Coleman Company, Denstsply International, I.E. Du Pont, Eastman Kodak, Honeywell Building Systems, Siemens Corp., Motorola, and Thomson Consumer Electronics.

Peter graduated from Rhode Island School of Design, receiving the Alcoa and Industrial Design Society of America Student Merit Awards.  He has served on the industrial design faculty at the Philadelphia College of Art and has been a guest lecturer at the Rhode Island School of Design, Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design, University of the Arts, Lehigh University, and Drexel University.  Peter has served as Juror for the ID Magazine Design Review, the Krups Awards, The Consumer Electronics Innovation Awards, the Reebok Designovation program and the Industrial Design Excellence Awards program, which he chaired in 1993.

The Industrial Design Society of America elected Peter its President in 1989, and in 1992 he was named a Fellow of the society.  He is past Board Chairperson of the Worldesign Foundation.  He was also a presenter at the United States Information Agency Design in America Eastern European Exhibit and has conducted lectures and seminars in Japan, Taiwan, France, and Italy.
<br>
		</td>
		
	</tr>
	
