		</td>
		
		<td width="20">&nbsp;</td>
		
		<td width="420" valign="top">		
		Carol Catalano is the founder and principal of Catalano Design, a Boston based industrial design firm that is active in many areas including consumer electronics, housewares, and home and office furnishings.  With over 20 years of experience, she has won a number of competitions, including, in 2001, "A Place to Sit", sponsored by Knoll International in partnership with Peabody Office Furniture and Adaptive Environments for her interactive Mambo Chair.  Her Capelli Stool, manufactured by Herman Miller, also won the Silver Prize in The International Furniture Design Competition Asahikawa in 1999 in Japan and a Silver IDEA award in 2002. In addition she holds a number of utility and design patents for consumer products and furniture. Her work has been published in I.D. Magazine, Abitare, Metropolis, Interiors, and the Boston Globe. 

Catalano's wide variety of clients has given her ample opportunity to apply her talents to a truly broad range of other products ranging from top quality car and home audio speakers to knives for professional cooks, and surge protectors for the consumer electronics market. 

She works closely with her clients to fully understand their culture, their technology, and their markets as well as focusing on their inevitable need to turn a healthy profit. 
<br>
