		Glen Walter is Co-founder (with Benjamin Beck, David Harting and Douglas Marsden) and Managing Member of (ELEVEN) a Boston based product development studio. In the world of “industrial design”, Glen is seen as a creative enthusiast and entrepreneur.  (ELEVEN) has gained international recognition by developing products for Microsoft, Procter & Gamble, Burton Snowboards, Herman Miller, Symbol Technologies, 3COM Motorola, OXO, Maytag, Cambridge Sound Works and many others.  Glen himself has been awarded an array of patents and has assembled numerous design awards for product development programs with which he has been directly involved.  He has successfully licensed a wide range of innovative consumer products. Glen has been extensively published and is a popular guest lecturer. He has presented at MIT, Harvard, Babson College, NYU, Syracuse Univ., Design Management Institute, IDSA and as a special guest to the government of Ireland.  He is a graduate of Syracuse University.  <br>
